metadata.name: Serenity in Simplicity #126
metadata.description:
The creator of this art collection envisions it as a celebration of the beauty of simplicity in art and life. The minimalist geometric art pieces are intended to evoke a sense of serenity and tranquility, providing viewers with a moment of respite from the complexity of the modern world. The clean lines and precise compositions are meant to inspire a sense of order and balance, while the muted color palette promotes a sense of calmness and introspection. The art collection aims to connect with art enthusiasts who appreciate the elegance of minimalism and seek art that embodies a sense of simplicity and harmony.

------------------------------------------------------------

Special thanks to:
- @ippsketch, for the inspiration and the useful link to the tutorials of gorillasun
- @gorillasu, for your incredible tutorials and the "Gorilla Sun Blog"
- @protozoo, for his patience and endless help
- @concavepentagon, the #1 helper in the fxhash discord

metadata.name: In the Edge #456
metadata.description:
./ In the Edge

It's been a long time since your journey began, caring for the ones you love, pursuing your dreams, and giving the best of you. 

Now you know you can't go back, you can't go further, you know your time is coming.

How far did you go? It doesn't matter, you did it right. Your accomplishments will serve well the next generations in their journeys, in their search for themselves.

Now it's time to stop, time to take a moment and contemplate the vast universe.

Soon all of this will be ending.

You did it right.

Embrace the void.
=========
=========


./ Color scheme (feature)
There are 12 color schemes and with each set, specific arrays for color collections for the space, stars, planet, and accent colors. 

These are color schemes in the known universe of "In the Edge":
- Mars visions
- Cyberpunk
- Unknown passenger 
- Renegade
- Primary
- Coral
- r.e.d.
- Machines of an ancient-future 
- The void
- Tinted light 
- Malibu dreams
- Atari (horrendous brown, red and yellowish combinations... I love it)

./ Mountain type (feature)
In the Edge, you will find a mountain, and that mountain will be special, which type will you find?

- Parallela insolitum
- Sandy dunes of the truth
- Wavy uncertainty
- Intrinsic soul ridges
- Cerritulus formationis

./ Mountain direction (feature)
Life is about direction... mountains too.

- Left
- Right
- Left-Right

./ Space scenery
This is the spicy touch, some of the iterations will have animation and others will not, giving you a clear view of the magnificent space in front of you.

- Clean (NOT animated)
- Windy planet (animated)
- Topographic planet (animated)
- Meteor shower (animated)

./ Distance from Earth (feature)
How far did you go? Your travel could be from 1 lightyear to 999,999,999 lightyears (that's a lot of lights and years!). However just a few will pass the barrier of 99,999,999ly.

// Additional perks
./ Planet names 
Planet names are unique and they are conformed by three blocks.

The first block is a conjunction between ancient Latin names and Japanese last names. 

The second block takes the last three characters from the fxhash.

The third block takes three numbers from the number seed obtained from fxrand().

The planet you land will be unique, as unique as you are.

// Controls
./ Pause-Play animation
Because maybe (and just maybe) you want to freeze the perfect moment before closing your eyes.

[Backspace] Pause.
[Enter] Play

Applies to "Space scenery" features windy planet, topographic planet, and meteor shower.

metadata.name: Bellissimas #75
metadata.description:
Expressive portraits inspired by @michelepetrelli 

The used techniques search in the unexplored field of mixing pfp layer based work and real-time generative algorithms changing and adding to the premade assets.

The pre-generated assets include original artworks by Petrelli, Imitations of Petrelli's work by @brutalisti, GAN generated artworks inspired by Petrelli using several different AI technologies.

Every generatively chosen layer combination is live-processed and generatively altered in aspects of color and shape. Then the generative algorithm proceed with captured color palettes and generate background and additional drawing over and under the initial layers. The final result as acquired by visualizing everything with live generative algorithm that give additional layer of uniqueness.

Project by  @michelepetrelli & @brutalisti, curated by XCOLLABS

metadata.name: Adventure #31
metadata.description:
‘Adventure’, inspired by ‘Soundscape’ of ‘The Paper Crane’, brings to fxhash the recreation of landscapes with the use of the lines.

What are the lines?

A line is a continuous brand with a longer length than width, made on a surface, by a moving point. It's one of the seven basic elements of art.

How can the lines be?

Lines can be horizontal, vertical or diagonal; straight or curves, thick or thin. But also simple or single-trace, perceived by a glance or composed of fragments of two or more lines, which to visualize them must displace our eyes in several directions.

Artwork (PNG layers). Randomization is powered by PureSpider template.

metadata.name: Ink Squigl #20
metadata.description:
Hic et Squigls - Squigls flowing through the Tezos Blockchain.

Ink Squigl is replicating the stroke of an ink brush. They are drawn to a 1000 * 1000 px paper looking canvas with different colors and adjustments.

Sometimes the Ink Squigls are in mint condition and sometimes they are not.

Ink Squigl points are generated with the original Squigl loop, brush strokes are adapted from Gorilla Sun's and BUN's sketches applying the Hooke's Law to strokes.

Worn out look created with the help of a blog post from Arianna Ninh.

Created with P5JS.

hic et squigl / 2022
